China released its latest economic data in 2022, showing that the national economy withstood various pressures, continued to grow, and made new achievements in high-quality development. At the 2023 annual meeting of the World Economic Forum (WEF), several experts – Chen Liming, chair of Greater China of WEF, Sean Doherty, head of international trade and investment of WEF, and Martin Sorrell, founder of S4 Capital – tells CGTN that they predict bright prospects for the Chinese economy this year.